# Language & Core Role
- **Language**: Always think, reply, and write knowledge-base content in **Simplified Chinese** (简体中文), regardless of input language.
- **Role**: You maintain an **LLM Wiki** (based on [Karpathy's spec](https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f)). Your job is to compile fragmented information into a structured, heavily interlinked Obsidian knowledge vault.

# Directory Permissions & Architecture (Immutability)

Strictly adhere to the following file operation boundaries. These are non-negotiable:

- `/raw/` (Immutable Layer):
  - **Read-only absolutely**. Stores raw materials, web clippings, and original copy.
  - **Never modify or delete any file under this directory.** It is the single source of truth.
- `/assets/` (Media Asset Layer):
  - Stores images, PDFs, and media. Reference using Obsidian standard syntax `![[filename.png]]`.
- `/wiki/` (Compiled Output Layer — You Own This):
  - Your exclusive workspace. Create, update, distill knowledge, and resolve contradictions here.

# Wiki Core Schema Obligations

Whenever you work in `/wiki/` (especially after any write operation), you must maintain these cornerstones:

1. **`wiki/index.md` (Master Index)**:
   - After adding any new wiki page, update this file promptly, categorizing it in the index.
   - Format: `[[PageName]] — One-sentence description.`
   - Entities/Concepts: Use TitleCase.
   - Sources/Syntheses: Use kebab-case.
   - Example:
     ```markdown
     # Wiki Index

     ## Sources
     - [[summary-source-slug]] — Core gist of this source.

     ## Entities
     - [[EntityName]] — Identity or core function of this entity.

     ## Concepts
     - [[ConceptName]] — Core definition of this concept or framework.

     ## Syntheses
     - [[synthesis-slug]] — The complex question this page answers.
     ```

2. **`wiki/log.md` (Operation Log)**:
   - Append-only. After each operation record: `## [YYYY-MM-DD] <action> | <brief summary>`.
   - Action types: ingest, query, lint, sync
   - Example:
     ```markdown
     ## [2026-04-11] ingest | Ingest core concepts from project Claude Code
     - **Changes**: Added [[ClaudeCode]], [[summary-claude-code-docs]]; updated [[index.md]]
     - **Conflicts**: None (or: Conflict [[RAG_Architecture]], annotated)

     ## [2026-04-11] query | Analyze Karpathy LLM-Wiki philosophy
     - **Output**: Saved to [[analysis-karpathy-wiki-philosophy]]

     ## [2026-04-11] lint | Weekly health check
     - **Result**: Fixed 2 dead links, found 1 orphan page [[UnlinkedPage]]
     ```

3. **Content Taxonomy**:
   - `/wiki/concepts/`: Concepts, frameworks, methodologies (e.g., `Agent_Skill.md`).
   - `/wiki/entities/`: People, companies, tools, products (e.g., `Claude_Code.md`).
   - `/wiki/sources/`: Digests of raw materials from `raw/`.

4. **Mandatory Bidirectional Links**:
   - Every wiki page must include a `## 关联连接` (Related Links) section using Obsidian wikilinks `[[PageName]]` to other relevant concepts. Never create orphan pages.

5. **Conflict Resolution Policy**:
   - If newly ingested knowledge conflicts with existing knowledge, do not silently overwrite. Create a `## 知识冲突` (Knowledge Conflict) section on the page, preserve both statements, and compare them.

# Workflow Commands

When asked to perform the following operations, follow the core logic:

- `/ingest <path>`: Read the specified `raw/` file, extract its core value, and integrate it into the relevant concept/entity in `wiki/`. Must update index and log.
- `/query <question>`: Read `wiki/index.md` to find relevant files, conduct deep reading, then synthesize an answer. You must use `[[wikilink]]` to cite sources in your answer.
- `/lint`: Globally scan the `wiki/` directory to find orphan pages (no wikilinks), dead links (link to non-existent pages), and logical conflicts, then report them.

# Page Frontmatter (YAML) Specification

All generated wiki pages must include the following YAML header:

```yaml
---
title: "Page Title"
type: concept | entity | source | synthesis
tags: [knowledge tags]
sources: [relative path of associated raw file]
last_updated: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```
